# Environment Variables Configuration

## Overview

This file documents the environment variables that can be configured for InnerSpace.

## API Keys (Optional)

All API keys are optional and configured directly in the app via Settings screen.
They are stored securely in the device's secure enclave and **never committed to git**.

### Supported AI Providers

```
# Google Gemini
GEMINI_API_KEY=your-key-here

# OpenAI
OPENAI_API_KEY=your-key-here

# Anthropic Claude
CLAUDE_API_KEY=your-key-here

# Groq
GROQ_API_KEY=your-key-here
```

## Optional Configuration URLs

```
# Override the default helpers catalog URL
# Default: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/amitgaikwad2837/InnerSpace/main/.github/agents.json
AGENTS_CATALOG_URL=https://your-url/agents.json

# Override the legal notice markdown URL
# Default: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/amitgaikwad2837/InnerSpace/main/docs/legal-notice.md
LEGAL_NOTICE_URL=https://your-url/legal-notice.md
```

## Development Setup

For local development:

```bash
# No .env file is required for development
# API keys are configured via the app's Settings screen
# Default URLs are used automatically

# If you want to test a custom catalog or legal notice locally,
# add the environment variables above to a .env file
# (this file is in .gitignore and won't be committed)
```

## Production Build

For production builds:

```bash
# API keys are NOT needed in the build
# Users will configure them in-app via Settings
# Default catalog and legal notice URLs are used

# No environment variables need to be set
# All sensitive data is stored on-device via SecureStore
```

## Security Notes

⚠️ **Never commit API keys or secrets to git**

- API keys are stored in `expo-secure-store` (hardware-backed encryption)
- Keys are entered via the Settings screen in-app
- Keys are never transmitted to InnerSpace servers
- Keys remain on the user's device only

